newsitem.title: USA: FOB Gulf Grain - Soy lower, some corn values down.
newsitem.headline: FOB Gulf Grain - Soy lower, some corn values down.

text.p: Nearby U.S. FOB Gulf soybean offers were lower Wednesday and some corn values were down in response to waning demand, exporters said.
"The market is weaker in the forwards because of a general lack of demand," said one exporter.
No fresh export news surfaced for the wheat market, and not much business was expected in the near term, wheat exporters said.
Record crops in Argentina and Brazil have left many predicting increased competition for the U.S. from those countries.
In recent corn business, South Korean buyers have purchased at least 76,000 tonnes of corn and the Philippines also bought corn from China.
Exporters said that the U.S. market was largely unconcerned with China's re-entry into the export market.
